column5: maybe I'm getting a message   The oath of many a fisher wife.

I spoiled myself this year for xmas...  Found myself a 2012 FJ CRuiser Trail Team Edition and bought it last week. If your not familiar with the Trail Team Edition there are only 200 made a year for Canada.  Here she is.    Also following on the hard to find theme I got a Japanese Curado made for jigging Tuna extra heavy drag.    A very good xmas!!!!!  If anyone is ionterested in a mint black FJ Cruiser my old one will be posted in the classified section!!
What a christmas you had!!!!!!Nice going!
Sweet machine.. Where did you find the solid black ice to hold it?
Lew,I hope yer not complaining. I know I wouldnt be. keep her happy.

Was able to spend yesterday with my elderly parents and have dinner with the family at the home we all grew up in. 24 for dinner, another 15 or so stopped in to wish all a Merry Christmas during the day.. It was the last meal there for us all as they are moving into a retirement residence in the new year. A dozen of us walked the neighborhood and we showed the Grandkids who lived where and who did this or that there. My wife and my gift was arranging it all and cooking the 40 pounds of turkey and of course the other 8 courses of food, man that's nuts. Everyone chipped in bringing food and cleaning up. Everyone except of course the few 20 something Italian Prince and Princesses, wouldn't want to take them away from their smart phones and wanting to know when we are going to open gifts because they were in a hurry to leave. I hope they enjoy their take out pizza next year.  If my wife and I need or should I say want stuff we go out and buy it. Stuff has absolutely nothing to do with Christmas.  I know it was supposed to be fishing related and is because we had a fish course for dinner as well.

I'm enjoying 9 days off work. Stress free, relaxing days with family is actually strange to get adjusted to but it's working wonders.  Oh yeah and a new IPad air, frogg togg wader jacket, aqua vu micro and hopefully 2-3 of ice fishing over the next week

A new spotter scope, a trucolor aim and point for my PPS 43C zombie killer and a promise for the 16 inch 9MM barrel from the machine shop. I was spoiled.  First off, my wife spent months getting approvals from manufacturers to create a fishing jersey and it looks awesome.  -molix supernato hybrid crankbaits in two different colors. -deadly black Megabass 110 jerkbait -autographed picture of Aaron Martens -Glacier Glove ultralight fishing gloves. -Shaman Chronarch CH150 -Ram mount for my trolling motor - a Plano 3650 filled with powerteam lures sick sticks in multiple colors.  For any if you lucky enough to deal with Paddletales Tackle in Winchester, I also got a Xmas stocking from there. I have gotten one of these every year for the last three years and they are awesome. They usually have about $70.00 of gear in them for about $20.00.  To say I was pretty stoked would be an understatement!  Adam
Wayne that is the best present any father would love. I was Welled up earlier when I saw the pics as you can not buy a present like that. All the best to you and the family.
